info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 12 at 9:13PM CDT until further notice by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Green Bay WI has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Wisconsin River below Alexander Reservoir affecting Lincoln County. ...FLOOD WARNING FOR SNOWMELT IN EFFECT FROM THIS EVENING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Wisconsin River below Alexander Reservoir. * WHEN...From this evening until further notice. * IMPACTS...At 1259.0 feet, Widespread wooded lowland flooding downstream of the dam. The river current downstream of the dam in Council Grounds Park is fast. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 9:10 PM CDT Wednesday the stage was 1259.4 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 9:10 PM CDT Wednesday was 1259.4 feet. - Forecast...No forecast is available for this location. - Flood stage is 1259.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 1258.0 feet on 10/16/2016. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued Thursday afternoon.
